/* Rules For defining/ Naming a variable:

1: The first charecter must be a letter or an underscore (_) or a Dollar symbol ($). We can't use a number as the first charecter.

2: The rest of the variable name can include any letter, any number or the underscore. Can't use any other Charecter including spaces.

Variable names are case sensitive.

No limit to the length of the variable name.

You can't use one of JavaScript's reserved words as a variable name.
*/